Patch Set 11:

> Patch Set 11: Code-Review-1
> 
> It looks like neither mysql nor postgres is being used in the tests:
> https://zuul.opendev.org/t/openstack/build/6fd0903d52af419daa2d386552d7de28/log/job-output.txt#996-1020

Brian,  are you saying that postgres/mysql should be used in the tests and that it isn't?
Or that the postgres/mysql setup shouldn't be done at all?

The postgres/mysql setup is something that glance does in its tools/test-setup.sh.  I don't know if its used in other glance test jobs or not.  I just fixed it so that if it is in fact being used, then the setup doesn't break.

If it isn't used at all in all the jobs, then we can add a separate patch to remove the setup altogether.
